# MUI Theme System and Styling Guidelines

1. Theme Configuration Priority:

   - Use theme tokens from src/theme/* configuration
   - Follow typography scale defined in theme.typography
   - Use spacing units from theme.spacing
   - Use color palette from theme.palette
   - Support dark/light mode with theme.palette.mode
   - Use theme.shape for consistent border radius
   - Use theme.shadows for elevation

2. Component Structure:

   - Use semantic HTML elements
   - Use Box for basic layouts
   - Use Stack for flex layouts
   - Use Grid for grid layouts
   - Use Typography for text styling
   - Keep components small and focused
   - Follow mobile-first approach

3. Styled Components Best Practices:

   - Use MUI's styled API with theme prop
   - Create styled components at file level
   - Follow naming convention: Styled[ComponentName]
   - Keep styled components close to their usage
   - Extend existing styled components when possible
   - Avoid nested selectors beyond 2 levels

4. Style Property Order:

   - Layout properties first (display, position, width, height)
   - Spacing properties second (margin, padding)
   - Visual properties last (color, background, border)
   - Group related properties together
   - Use theme values for consistency

5. Performance & Accessibility:

   - Minimize style recalculations
   - Avoid unnecessary nesting
   - Ensure proper color contrast
   - Implement proper focus states
   - Support keyboard navigation
   - Use proper ARIA attributes
   - Follow WCAG guidelines

6. Common Patterns:

   - Implement consistent spacing rhythm
   - Follow typography hierarchy
   - Use proper color contrast ratios
   - Use theme.transitions for animations
   - Consider RTL support
   - Use proper error states
   - Handle loading states
   - Implement responsive designs 